@startuml Security_Authentication
skinparam monochrome true
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam maxMessageSize 150
skinparam ParticipantPadding 20
skinparam BoxPadding 10

title Cybersecurity Focus: Authentication & Session Management

box "Client Side" #f9f9f9
actor "User (Patient/Doctor)" as User
participant "Browser" as Browser
end box

box "Server Side (Flask)" #e6f7ff
participant "WTForms\n(CSRF Protection)" as WTF
participant "Auth Blueprint" as Auth
participant "Werkzeug Security\n(PBKDF2/scrypt)" as Werkzeug
participant "Flask-Login\n(Session Manager)" as Session
end box

database "SQLite Database" as DB

== Registration (Secure Password Storage) ==
User -> Browser : Enters details & Password
Browser -> Auth : POST /auth/register (Form Data)
activate Auth

Auth -> WTF : validate_on_submit()
note right of WTF: Validates CSRF token\nprevents Cross-Site Request Forgery
WTF --> Auth : is_valid = True

Auth -> Werkzeug : generate_password_hash(password)
note right of Werkzeug: Uses PBKDF2:sha256\nor scrypt algorithm.\nAutomatically generates & appends a salt.
Werkzeug --> Auth : password_hash (Salt + Hash)

Auth -> DB : Store User (username, password_hash)
DB --> Auth : Success
Auth --> Browser : Redirect to Login
deactivate Auth

== Login (Authentication & Session) ==
User -> Browser : Enters Username & Password
Browser -> Auth : POST /auth/login
activate Auth

Auth -> DB : Fetch User by Username
DB --> Auth : User Record (includes password_hash)

Auth -> Werkzeug : check_password_hash(stored_hash, input_password)
note right of Werkzeug: Extracts salt from stored_hash.\nHashes input_password with salt.\nCompares using constant-time\nstring comparison (prevents timing attacks).
Werkzeug --> Auth : True (Match)

Auth -> Session : login_user(User)
note right of Session: Generates a cryptographically\nsecure session ID.
Session -> Browser : Set-Cookie: session=SecureToken; HttpOnly; SameSite=Lax
note left of Browser: HttpOnly prevents XSS theft.\nSameSite prevents CSRF.
Auth --> Browser : Redirect to Dashboard
deactivate Auth
@enduml

@startuml Security_Encryption
skinparam monochrome true
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam maxMessageSize 150
skinparam ParticipantPadding 20
skinparam BoxPadding 10

title Cybersecurity Focus: Medical Report Encryption at Rest (AES-256-GCM)

actor Doctor
participant "Doctor Blueprint" as API
participant "Cryptography Library\n(Hazmat Primitives)" as Crypto
database "SQLite Database" as DB
participant "Local File System\n(storage/reports/)" as FS
actor Patient

== Encrypting Sensitive Medical Data ==
Doctor -> API : Uploads Medical Report (File)
activate API

API -> Crypto : AESGCM.generate_key(bit_length=256)
note right of Crypto: Generates cryptographically\nsecure random 256-bit key.
Crypto --> API : raw_key (32 bytes)
API -> API : base64_encode(raw_key) -> base64_key

API -> Crypto : os.urandom(12)
Crypto --> API : Nonce (12 bytes)
note right of Crypto: GCM mode requires a unique\nnonce for every encryption operation.

API -> Crypto : AESGCM(raw_key).encrypt(nonce, plaintext_file, None)
note right of Crypto: Authenticated Encryption with Associated Data (AEAD).\nProvides both Confidentiality (encryption)\nand Integrity (MAC authentication tag).
Crypto --> API : ciphertext + 16-byte MAC Tag

API -> API : Combine: final_bytes = nonce + ciphertext + tag
API -> FS : Write final_bytes to UUID.enc
FS --> API : File stored on disk

API -> DB : Store metadata:\n- encrypted_file_path\n- base64_key (DEK)
note right of DB: Key is stored in DB, while\nciphertext is on disk. This separates\nthe encrypted data from the key.
DB --> API : Success
deactivate API

== Decrypting Medical Data for Authorized User ==
Patient -> API : Request File Download
activate API

API -> DB : Fetch Report metadata (base64_key, file_path)
DB --> API : Metadata

API -> FS : Read bytes from UUID.enc
FS --> API : final_bytes (nonce + ciphertext + tag)

API -> API : Extract Nonce (first 12 bytes)\nExtract Ciphertext+Tag (remaining bytes)

API -> Crypto : AESGCM(raw_key).decrypt(nonce, ciphertext_and_tag, None)
note right of Crypto: Cryptography lib calculates MAC of ciphertext.\nIf it doesn't match the appended Tag,\nit raises InvalidTag error (prevents tampering).
Crypto --> API : plaintext_file_bytes

API --> Patient : Serve Decrypted File
deactivate API
@enduml
